Context: To attend a group at George Brown College for better management of thoughts, behaviors, and emotions, one must book an intake appointment with a counsellor by emailing letstalk@georgebrown.ca or using the Counselling Student Portal. The groups focus on wellness skill-building. Application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more can be kept up-to-date by signing up. Contact information: 416-415-2000 (voice) and 1-877-515-5559 (TTY), or email ask.george@georgebrown.ca. Social media hub is also available for more information. Note that the information on this website may change without notice, and students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
